"No workers, boss do it yourself, " read Vivian Luo's accompanying video, which she had just posted on Wechat's social network. In the video, Vivian's father is in the garment workshop, ironing clothes with a few workers.

The Vivian factory has been back in production for two or three days, but there is still a serious shortage of workers. Wei Anne father and daughter had to fight together, "my father burned two, I burned the afternoon. "

Vivian's family run Huzhou Zhili Pretty Girl Clothing Co. , Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as pretty girl) is a medium-sized children's clothing enterprises in Zhili town, such as pretty girl size children's clothing enterprises in Zhili town there are about 1,000.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhili town is a famous children's clothing production center in China. According to incomplete statistics, there are 13,000 children's clothing production and processing units in the town, 7,000 e-commerce, and 2,000 to 3,000 clothing supporting units. In 2018, the annual sales volume of children's clothing in Zhili town reached 55 billion yuan.

However, now affected by the new pneumonia epidemic, the contract of China's children's wear market 60% of the children's wear town is facing a severe production test. The situation at the Children's clothing factory in Zhili is not good.

###Eighty percent of the workers in an enterprise can not return to work

According to the normal production schedule, children's clothing enterprises mostly in March to complete the production and marketing of Spring Children's clothing, is currently carrying out the production of summer children's clothing.

But this year the unexpected COVID-19 has thrown off plans, and production at the factory has been sharply delayed for the summer. The town's businesses have been back to work since late February, but capacity is nowhere near the levels it reached a year ago.

More than the town's Children's clothing business owners told interface fashion, one of the biggest difficulties is a shortage of labor.

Incomparable Clothing Limited Company (hereinafter referred to as incomparable) is a scale and production capacity are in the forefront of the town of Zhili Children's wear enterprises.

Now, ineffable managers are back on the job, but only about 20% of the workers are back. INEFFABLE chairman and General Manager Zhu Huiqiang to interface fashion frankly, "every production line can basically move up slowly, the speed is very slow. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The town of Zhili is full of migrant workers. The town is only 90 square kilometers, but there are 450,000 people, including 100,000 migrant workers. From factory workers to business owners, from the factory to the enterprise management and operation of each link in the industrial chain there are outsiders.

But in the epidemic, highly dependent on migrant workers in the weaving of Children's clothing manufacturers have become difficult.

In mid-february, a number of cities in Zhejiang Province launched a "people-snatching war" , including Zhili town of Huzhou Wuxing District government. Huzhou's municipal government on February 16 unveiled a series of incentives to return to work, including a subsidy of no less than 100 million yuan, a one-off living allowance of 1,000 yuan per person for new hires, according to prism.

More importantly, the government will fully subsidize all the expenses incurred by enterprises in organizing the return of field workers by charter bus. Wuxing District also confirmed that Chunqiu Airlines would act as a charter carrier to pick up migrant workers.

Thousands of migrant workers have been brought back to Zhili in this way, but a large number of workers are still stranded at home for various reasons.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The town of Zhili organized buses to take the workers back. Photograph: Huzhou Daily

INEFFABLE also organized the return of the workers by car, but the effect was not so good, mainly because "the workers were not concentrated and did not pile up. " Zhu Huiqiang told interface fashion, "The key thing is that she doesn't want to come, or he doesn't put things in certain places. Everything. "

Women are especially needed in the garment factories. But many primary and secondary schools are now starting later, with the result that female workers are reluctant to leave their children behind.

"When the children can go to school, this group of people may come to work, " Huang Kangliang, president of Hangzhou Weilan Zhiyi Technology Co. , Ltd. , told interface fashion.

###Increased segregation of migrant workers

The shortage of workers has hit the self-employed in Zhili's "front shop and back factory" model even harder. In Zhili town, "front shop after factory" refers to children's clothing self-employed in a two-or three-storey building, set up as storefronts along the street, showing the production of children's clothing, while the Interior for Children's clothing production work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A Street of Children's clothing stores in Zhili

The outbreak is one of the main reasons workers are unable to return home. On the other hand, although the owners of the Children's clothing businesses in Zhili are willing to pay a premium for workers, many choose to work in factories near their home towns, given the relatively high cost of living in the town.

For example, Anhui, which has traditionally sent a large number of female workers to Zhili, has seen a return of labor in recent years. This outbreak has arguably exacerbated the situation.

The partners and workers of Cerulean are concentrated in Anhui, where labor costs are lower. The company has developed a children's clothing supply chain platform, "Kuai Yi" , to help children's clothing brands and manufacturers online docking, to achieve the split clothing production process and online organization of production purposes.

So far, the platform has gathered 100 or 200 manufacturers, management of the workers to four thousand people. According to Huang Kangliang, these Anhui workers choose to return to work near the factory.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photograph: Huzhou Daily

In recent years, the town of Zhili Children's clothing manufacturing industry is undergoing transformation and upgrading. And some can not keep up with the transformation of the self-employed, their orders eventually transferred to other supply chain model more advantageous enterprises. Kuai Yi platform belongs to the latter.

From the "original commissioned design (ODM ) " model further evolved, "express clothing" platform commissioned by the brand to express clothing manufacturers commissioned third-party production and post-maintenance, and the platform plays the role of procurement and sales. In other words, as long as the express platform can deliver materials such as fabrics and accessories to manufacturers in Anhui, local manufacturers can organize workers to carry out production.

"It turned out that I would bet a month's worth of goods on him and say that he had one raw material, " Huang told the interface reporter, "To put it bluntly, whenever a worker can get out of the car, he can do it without too much impact on purchasing. "

When the town of Zhili Children's clothing self-employed hard to recruit workers, "fast clothes" but "in short supply" and distress. "The pressure is there, but it's a lot more pressure that we can't handle right now. "

###How to make up for it

Several children's wear business owners predict that the full return of workers may have to wait until mid-to-late March. At the same time, the face of the situation is still there, and the price of fabrics also followed by the problem.

Under heavy pressure, part of the town children's clothing factories have chosen to completely shut down in the first half. Most of these manufacturers only produce spot, the loss is only part of the rent, plant closure can limit losses.

The futures brands chose to stick with it, even though it meant they had to deal with extremely complicated situations.

On the one hand, children's clothing compared to the ready-to-wear market more sensitive to seasonal weather and so on. Generally speaking, the summer children's clothing comes into the market before May and June of each year. This means that this year, Zhili town children's clothing manufacturers summer production cycle will be greatly compressed, production pressure increased.

On the other hand, when the terminal price of the futures is fixed, once the manufacturing cost rises, the futures manufacturers can only reduce the output, and then further affect the sales scale.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhu Huiqiang told interface fashion, in previous years to April, can not be compared to the complete summer children's clothing production and marketing work. According to this year's situation, "production I estimate to be able to reach 70% , is already very good. " Can Not be compared to the operation of a direct-based children's clothing brand BCOBI and children's clothing wholesale brand "Camillo. ".

And the first half of the impact on children's wear enterprises, as well as children's wear market downturn may also affect the entire industry in the second half of the order size and production and marketing plans.

"So for the whole year, for those who do futures, for brand companies, this year's loss is quite big, " Zhu said

The outbreak is also testing the town of Zhili Children's clothing factory's ability to resist risk and crisis management.

The Children's clothing industry in Zhili is a "rugby" structure. Last year, under the overall economic situation, the town enterprises realized 30% of the children's wear enterprises guaranteed profit, 20% do not make a loss, and 20% or 30% of enterprises near the break-even line of the benign situation.

Thanks to the novelty-seeking Children's wear business in Zhili.

Can Not be compared to just last year to adjust the supply chain model, from the original "full futures" model to "70% futures + 30% spot" model transformation. "We may have 50 percent of the futures and 50 percent of the spot from next year, " Zhu said in an interview with the interface reporter last year

This forward-looking Paradigm Shift could help the company reduce its losses this year. "We are now going to reduce the futures by 20 to 30 percent, " Zhu told ifashion. "When the workers come back, we are going to replenish them from the spot. "

In sales, can not be compared to the current has resumed business of direct and agency stores only 10% of the total. However, "a lot of customers also said that I opened, is also no business. "

Therefore, can not be compared to trying online community and private marketing, Zhu Huiqiang also plans to "let every store do small live. See if there is a breakthrough. "
